[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man held as £40,000 of crack cocaine recovered in Aberdeen

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Crack cocaine with an estimated street value of more than £40,000 has been recovered in Aberdeen.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Police Scotland said the seizure was made at an address in the Kittybrewster area on Wednesday.
A 45-year-old man from the London area has been charged.
He is expected to appear at Aberdeen Sheriff Court on Thursday.
